Therefore, $k = 4 \sqrt{5},$ so $\det \mathbf{D} = k = 4 \sqrt{5},$ which means $\mathbf{D}$ scales the plane by a factor of $4 \sqrt{5}.$  Hence, $\mathbf{D} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \sqrt{5} & 0 \\ 0 & 4 \sqrt{5} \end{pmatrix}.$

Then
\[\mathbf{R} \mathbf{D} = \mathbf{R} \begin{pmatrix} 4 \sqrt{5} & 0 \\ 0 & 4 \sqrt{5} \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 8 & -4 \\ 4 & 8 \end{pmatrix}.\]Hence,
\[\mathbf{R} = \begin{pmatrix} \cos \theta & -\sin \theta \\ \sin \theta & \cos \theta \end{pmatrix}.\]Then
\[\tan \theta = \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta} = \boxed{\frac{1}{2}}.\]

