Let $\mathbf{p} = \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix}.$  Then
\[\mathbf{p} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{7}{17} \begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -\frac{28}{17} \\ \frac{7}{17} \end{pmatrix}}.\]

Let $\mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}.$  Let $\mathbf{p}$ be the projection of $\mathbf{a}$ onto $\mathbf{b}.$

[asy]
usepackage("amsmath");

